section.section:
The Department may issue an order of impoundment and immediately impound drugs or prescription records of a permit holder or an authorized prescriber if:
A permit holder's permit or authorized prescriber's license has expired or has been revoked or suspended;
An application for a permit or license has been denied;
A board has:
Determined that the permit holder or authorized prescriber failed to comply with a board order, letter of surrender, or law regarding the disposition of drugs or prescription records; and
Requested that the Department impound the drugs or prescription records;
The drugs pose an imminent threat to the public health, safety, or welfare; or
The confidentiality of the prescription records is in imminent danger of being compromised.

Except as otherwise provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Department shall:
Attempt to serve written notice of an impoundment on the permit holder or authorized prescriber;
Provide the permit holder or authorized prescriber with an opportunity to avoid impoundment by allowing the permit holder or authorized prescriber to dispose of the drugs or prescription records in a manner acceptable to the Department;
Provide the permit holder or authorized prescriber with an opportunity prior to impoundment to review the nature, type, and amount of information upon which the Department issued the impoundment order; and
Provide the permit holder or authorized prescriber with an opportunity to avoid impoundment by providing the Department with information upon which the Department could reasonably conclude that the impoundment is not warranted.
